274
00:14:20,480 --> 00:14:21,710
Papa's treat.

275
00:14:24,620 --> 00:14:26,770
Then, I'd like one more Peking duck.

276
00:14:26,910 --> 00:14:27,520
Mm.

277
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:29,240
- Alright.
- The whole thing's mine.

278
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:34,580
- Come on, come on, let's eat.
- Alright, let's eat.

279
00:14:38,540 --> 00:14:39,670
Moo, what about you, dear?

280
00:14:40,490 --> 00:14:41,430
What would you like to eat?

281
00:14:41,800 --> 00:14:44,110
Uh, I'd like a bamboo pith soup, then.

282
00:14:47,620 --> 00:14:48,490
Eat up, kids.

283
00:14:48,530 --> 00:14:49,530
Eat up, eat up.

284
00:14:50,560 --> 00:14:51,280
Yeah.

285
00:14:53,920 --> 00:14:56,160
I'm so happy.

286
00:15:09,400 --> 00:15:11,010
Here's your bamboo pith soup.

287
00:15:18,800 --> 00:15:20,720
Papa, do you like
stir-fried chicken with cashew nuts?

288
00:15:30,310 --> 00:15:31,960
He definitely does.

289
00:15:32,860 --> 00:15:34,210
Eat up, darling.

290
00:15:43,570 --> 00:15:44,380
How was it?

291
00:15:45,900 --> 00:15:48,100
What do you think?
I'm nervous as hell right now.

292
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:52,080
Hey, come on.

293
00:15:52,120 --> 00:15:53,120
It's gonna be fine.

294
00:15:53,150 --> 00:15:53,980
What's that?

295
00:15:54,930 --> 00:15:56,170
"Come on", my ass.

296
00:15:58,120 --> 00:16:00,520
I hope your papa doesn't hate me too much.

297
00:16:01,510 --> 00:16:02,310
He won't.

298
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:04,410
He's just acting tough, that's all.

299
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:06,800
Tai,

300
00:16:08,230 --> 00:16:10,040
don't be such a know-it-all.

301
00:16:11,670 --> 00:16:12,390
Papa...
Just go for now.

302
00:16:20,440 --> 00:16:22,090
Now that I've seen Moo,

303
00:16:22,410 --> 00:16:26,080
I can see why you chose him.

304
00:16:27,500 --> 00:16:28,710
He's adorable, isn't he?

305
00:16:29,010 --> 00:16:30,410
Very much so!

306
00:16:33,880 --> 00:16:34,520
Tai!

307
00:16:35,020 --> 00:16:36,020
What's wrong?

308
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:37,120
You look like you've seen a ghost.

309
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:40,760
It's Papa!

310
00:16:40,850 --> 00:16:42,110
Let me be frank with you.

311
00:16:43,410 --> 00:16:44,170
Well...

312
00:16:45,700 --> 00:16:47,310
I don't want you two to be together.

313
00:16:49,560 --> 00:16:51,110
It's not that I'm disgusted or anything,

314
00:16:52,650 --> 00:16:54,300
but Fu is an executive.

315
00:16:55,170 --> 00:16:57,500
For him to be with just an intern,

316
00:16:58,490 --> 00:16:59,400
it's...

317
00:17:00,410 --> 00:17:01,570
it's just too different a world.

318
00:17:04,620 --> 00:17:05,910
If you understand,

319
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:08,050
you should let him go.

320
00:17:09,050 --> 00:17:10,110
I do understand.

321
00:17:10,990 --> 00:17:11,780
But sir,

322
00:17:12,410 --> 00:17:13,410
I myself

323
00:17:13,570 --> 00:17:15,620
won't be an intern forever.

324
00:17:15,830 --> 00:17:16,580
One day,

325
00:17:16,730 --> 00:17:19,760
I will be the owner of a hotel
no less grand than Golden Peony Hotel.

326
00:17:21,470 --> 00:17:23,880
And I promise
I won't be a disgrace to Fu's name.

327
00:17:24,540 --> 00:17:26,020
You're a confident one.

328
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:30,110
Honestly, I don't know what the future holds,

329
00:17:31,770 --> 00:17:32,820
but at least

330
00:17:33,110 --> 00:17:35,430
I believe it's possible.

331
00:17:36,570 --> 00:17:38,370
Though if you want me to let go of Fu,

332
00:17:38,730 --> 00:17:39,780
I can't do that.

333
00:17:43,040 --> 00:17:44,280
To me,

334
00:17:44,510 --> 00:17:46,070
letting Moo go

335
00:17:46,460 --> 00:17:48,090
is just as impossible, Papa.

336
00:17:49,300 --> 00:17:50,300
Because Moo...

337
00:17:50,760 --> 00:17:52,320
is the one my heart belongs to.

338
00:17:55,130 --> 00:17:56,380
Please give us a chance.

339
00:17:56,460 --> 00:17:57,030
I...

340
00:17:57,490 --> 00:18:00,200
will prove myself
to be worthy of your trust, sir.

341
00:18:14,260 --> 00:18:16,910
Here comes Tee Lek's dish!

342
00:18:18,750 --> 00:18:21,680
Wow, dessert is here!

343
00:18:22,800 --> 00:18:24,480
Go on, scoop some for Moo,

344
00:18:24,510 --> 00:18:25,480
so he can eat more.

345
00:18:29,010 --> 00:18:29,600
Of course.

346
00:18:31,540 --> 00:18:32,910
Here you go.

347
00:18:32,960 --> 00:18:34,390
There.

348
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:41,600
There!

349
00:18:41,830 --> 00:18:44,750
Tee, go easy on it, or you'll choke!

350
00:18:45,990 --> 00:18:47,510
Look at you!

351
00:18:49,140 --> 00:18:51,560
Ahhh!

352
00:18:51,640 --> 00:18:53,280
Ooh, oh, oh...

353
00:19:07,320 --> 00:19:09,670
Fu has already grown up, darling.

354
00:19:10,410 --> 00:19:13,010
Let him follow his own heart for a change.

355
00:19:13,590 --> 00:19:15,210
At least for this.

356
00:19:16,930 --> 00:19:18,410
All this time,

357
00:19:18,840 --> 00:19:21,170
he's never asked for anything,

358
00:19:21,390 --> 00:19:23,280
and he's always been a good boy.

359
00:19:23,800 --> 00:19:26,380
Maybe you should give them a chance.

360
00:19:26,590 --> 00:19:28,690
Fu is my son.

361
00:19:29,450 --> 00:19:31,990
I know exactly what kind of person he is.

362
00:19:32,920 --> 00:19:34,910
You don't have to tell me twice.

363
00:19:59,420 --> 00:20:00,790
Are you okay, Moo?

364
00:20:01,920 --> 00:20:02,920
I am.

365
00:20:03,490 --> 00:20:04,590
Why would you ask that?

366
00:20:12,260 --> 00:20:13,400
Even though Papa is strict...

367
00:20:15,390 --> 00:20:17,910
don't leave me, please?

368
00:20:26,510 --> 00:20:27,510
Then...

369
00:20:27,820 --> 00:20:29,390
let's be together forever.

370
00:20:30,100 --> 00:20:30,810
How does that sound?

371
00:20:32,800 --> 00:20:34,690
Thank you, Moo-Moo.

372
00:20:35,640 --> 00:20:37,720
I never get lonely because of you.

373
00:20:45,020 --> 00:20:46,700
Are you home alone today?

374
00:20:47,730 --> 00:20:49,090
Yeah. Why?

375
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:52,810
Then...

376
00:20:55,890 --> 00:20:56,890
You perv.

377
00:20:58,350 --> 00:20:59,280
Just kidding.

378
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:00,730
Well,

379
00:21:01,020 --> 00:21:04,190
I just wanted
to introduce myself to your family.

380
00:21:06,900 --> 00:21:08,820
When everyone's home,

381
00:21:09,170 --> 00:21:10,510
I'll bring you back here again.

382
00:21:11,980 --> 00:21:14,190
Can't we just do a trial run today?

383
00:21:16,630 --> 00:21:17,560
Fu!

384
00:21:21,990 --> 00:21:23,200
Good night, Fu.

385
00:21:28,390 --> 00:21:29,010
Moo,

386
00:21:30,880 --> 00:21:32,380
I'm gonna kiss your cheek now.

387
00:21:57,230 --> 00:21:58,230
Good night.

388
00:21:59,250 --> 00:22:00,090
I'd better go.

389
00:22:30,700 --> 00:22:31,380
Hey,

390
00:22:32,010 --> 00:22:34,800
it seems like Fu wants to meet my family.

391
00:22:36,800 --> 00:22:38,000
And what's the problem?

392
00:22:38,800 --> 00:22:39,800
I'm embarrassed!

393
00:22:39,970 --> 00:22:40,970
My family

394
00:22:41,080 --> 00:22:43,500
gets so freaking chaotic
whenever we get together.

395
00:22:44,990 --> 00:22:46,580
Plus, they're all weirdos.

396
00:22:46,640 --> 00:22:48,190
Do you think
Fu will be able to accept that?

397
00:22:48,940 --> 00:22:50,590
I don't think he's gonna see it that way.

398
00:22:50,890 --> 00:22:51,830
Who knows?

399
00:22:52,050 --> 00:22:54,270
Maybe he might even
get along well with your family,

400
00:22:54,400 --> 00:22:55,940
since you said they're all weirdos.

401
00:22:57,290 --> 00:22:57,990
Mm.

402
00:23:01,470 --> 00:23:02,290
You know?

403
00:23:04,360 --> 00:23:06,300
Apart from being weird,

404
00:23:07,600 --> 00:23:10,000
he's also very lonely.

405
00:23:11,520 --> 00:23:12,520
Lonely?

406
00:23:14,010 --> 00:23:14,720
Ever since he was a child,

407
00:23:16,210 --> 00:23:18,100
he's always been alone.

408
00:23:20,300 --> 00:23:22,180
Before our family got to where it is now,

409
00:23:23,660 --> 00:23:25,900
Papa and Mama
had to fly to Hong Kong for work so often.

410
00:23:27,040 --> 00:23:29,480
That's why he spent
most of his time with Mimi,

411
00:23:30,800 --> 00:23:32,510
which is why they were so close.

412
00:23:38,760 --> 00:23:39,840
Is it delicious?

413
00:23:40,200 --> 00:23:41,360
It is, it is.

414
00:23:41,420 --> 00:23:43,300
Your food is the best!

415
00:23:45,440 --> 00:23:47,700
I gave it my all!

416
00:23:48,520 --> 00:23:49,900
Eat up, dear.

417
00:24:04,910 --> 00:24:07,800
Wow, you've got great skills.

418
00:24:13,020 --> 00:24:14,040
Keep pressing.

419
00:24:15,440 --> 00:24:18,680
I want you to be
with your Fu-Fu a long time, Mimi.

420
00:24:19,290 --> 00:24:21,310
Mimi will stay healthy

421
00:24:21,460 --> 00:24:24,040
so she can be with you a long time!

422
00:24:25,100 --> 00:24:26,700
But once Mimi passed away,

423
00:24:27,240 --> 00:24:28,610
Fu's whole world

424
00:24:28,970 --> 00:24:30,400
was consumed by loneliness.

425
00:24:32,340 --> 00:24:34,500
Fu, where is Mimi?

426
00:24:34,900 --> 00:24:36,800
Mimi is gone.

427
00:24:43,090 --> 00:24:44,400
But since he was the eldest brother,

428
00:24:45,810 --> 00:24:47,630
he had to put on a brave face,

429
00:24:48,120 --> 00:24:49,510
so he could
take care of his little brothers.

430
00:24:52,110 --> 00:24:54,700
He never had the chance
to enjoy his childhood,

431
00:24:55,720 --> 00:24:57,890
never had time to be weak,

432
00:24:58,940 --> 00:25:00,420
to be fussy,

433
00:25:01,090 --> 00:25:02,320
or to be affectionate with anyone.

434
00:25:07,210 --> 00:25:08,700
Until he met you.

435
00:25:13,080 --> 00:25:13,980
So...

436
00:25:14,310 --> 00:25:15,510
don't worry about it.

437
00:25:19,960 --> 00:25:20,690
But...

438
00:25:21,700 --> 00:25:23,300
I am worried about one thing.

439
00:25:27,640 --> 00:25:28,600
- Lhee!
- Lhee!

440
00:25:43,500 --> 00:25:44,310
Whoa...

441
00:26:03,500 --> 00:26:04,490
Jeez...

442
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:06,880
You're taking extra Japanese classes.

443
00:26:07,210 --> 00:26:07,940
And what's this?

444
00:26:08,110 --> 00:26:09,000
Your lover gave it to you?

445
00:26:09,990 --> 00:26:11,030
Are they also Japanese?

446
00:26:12,110 --> 00:26:13,610
Japanese or not,
it's none of your concern.

447
00:26:14,110 --> 00:26:14,840
Give it back.

448
00:26:31,970 --> 00:26:32,750
Hurry.

449
00:26:35,880 --> 00:26:36,880
Is everyone present?

450
00:26:39,590 --> 00:26:42,560
We're having
a physical fitness assessment today.

451
00:26:42,600 --> 00:26:44,220
Everyone, partner up and get in line.

452
00:26:44,640 --> 00:26:45,310
Start.

453
00:26:46,380 --> 00:26:47,480
Tee, wanna be my partner?

454
00:26:47,580 --> 00:26:48,110
No.

455
00:26:48,400 --> 00:26:49,790
Hey, Tee. Wanna be my partner?

456
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:50,580
No.

457
00:26:50,610 --> 00:26:53,210
- You can be with James!
- Come on, dude...

458
00:27:05,470 --> 00:27:07,440
You have so many friends,
so why pair up with me?

459
00:27:07,610 --> 00:27:09,960
As if you have any friends to pair up with.

460
00:27:15,570 --> 00:27:16,800
Is your baby really Japanese?

461
00:27:20,530 --> 00:27:21,870
Is their name Doraemon?

462
00:27:24,020 --> 00:27:25,020
Why aren't you saying something?

463
00:27:25,290 --> 00:27:26,010
Flustered?

464
00:27:28,310 --> 00:27:29,760
Tanjiro, Gojo, Nobita,

465
00:27:29,790 --> 00:27:30,670
Conan, or Arale?

466
00:27:30,960 --> 00:27:31,820
Cut it out!

467
00:27:32,960 --> 00:27:33,750
Or what?

468
00:27:37,170 --> 00:27:37,900
Ow!

469
00:27:41,510 --> 00:27:43,220
Jeab, I...

470
00:27:43,410 --> 00:27:45,600
Shit, Jeab is legit bleeding.

471
00:27:46,360 --> 00:27:48,680
Tee's mouth must be impossible
to pry open; it didn't even bleed.

472
00:28:00,900 --> 00:28:01,820
Fu!

473
00:28:02,120 --> 00:28:03,810
- Hm?
- I've brought you hot cocoa.

474
00:28:04,000 --> 00:28:05,310
Oh, thank you, Moo.

475
00:28:05,730 --> 00:28:06,730
Have a seat.

476
00:28:09,940 --> 00:28:12,440
Uh, Fu. So...

477
00:28:13,250 --> 00:28:14,410
This weekend,

478
00:28:15,610 --> 00:28:17,110
my dad will come to visit home,

479
00:28:17,600 --> 00:28:18,600
and...

480
00:28:18,840 --> 00:28:20,300
my mom will also be there.

481
00:28:21,640 --> 00:28:24,800
As for my older sister,
she's free, so she wants to come as well.

482
00:28:26,050 --> 00:28:28,170
So I'm thinking that you...

483
00:28:28,380 --> 00:28:28,930
I'm coming.

484
00:28:30,030 --> 00:28:31,970
I've always wanted to meet your family.

485
00:28:34,930 --> 00:28:35,810
Shit,

486
00:28:36,310 --> 00:28:37,520
how am I gonna deal with Lhee?

487
00:28:38,540 --> 00:28:39,230
What did you say?
Huh?

488
00:28:39,850 --> 00:28:41,210
Oh, nothing.

489
00:28:41,290 --> 00:28:42,090
I just said...

490
00:28:42,630 --> 00:28:43,630
Sri.

491
00:28:43,810 --> 00:28:44,500
Sri?

492
00:28:44,540 --> 00:28:46,680
Sri's rice porridge shop is really good.

493
00:28:47,990 --> 00:28:49,700
- Oh...
- Try it out if you have time.

494
00:28:49,950 --> 00:28:52,310
Yeah, let's go. Anywhere you want to.

495
00:28:52,460 --> 00:28:54,880
I'm hungry. I'm gonna get off work now.

496
00:28:55,480 --> 00:28:57,030
Let's go to Sri's rice porridge shop.

497
00:29:01,410 --> 00:29:01,990
Whoa...

498
00:29:09,580 --> 00:29:10,810
Little Chicken,
Little Chicken, Little Chicken!

499
00:29:37,060 --> 00:29:37,700
Here.

500
00:29:42,820 --> 00:29:43,760
Are you feeling better now?

501
00:29:45,650 --> 00:29:46,390
Well...

502
00:29:47,040 --> 00:29:48,040
Yeah, I am.

503
00:29:50,230 --> 00:29:51,790
Is there anything you want to vent about?

504
00:29:52,370 --> 00:29:53,410
You can talk to me.

505
00:29:55,190 --> 00:29:56,190
Well...

506
00:29:56,310 --> 00:29:58,180
I want to change schools, Yu.

507
00:29:59,920 --> 00:30:01,500
At school, there's this kid

508
00:30:02,020 --> 00:30:03,500
who always messes with me.

509
00:30:04,960 --> 00:30:06,720
At first, I didn't care that much

510
00:30:07,740 --> 00:30:10,100
because he actually
had a decent side to him.

511
00:30:13,990 --> 00:30:16,420
But it has been getting worse and worse

512
00:30:18,450 --> 00:30:20,190
until I can't stand it anymore.

513
00:30:24,390 --> 00:30:24,840
Wait,

514
00:30:25,360 --> 00:30:26,870
has he done anything harmful to you, Jeab?

515
00:30:27,940 --> 00:30:29,060
This is...

516
00:30:29,420 --> 00:30:30,520
from an accident, Yu.

517
00:30:37,040 --> 00:30:37,810
Yu,

518
00:30:39,800 --> 00:30:41,520
am I just running away from my problems

519
00:30:42,620 --> 00:30:44,290
if I want to change schools?

520
00:30:45,820 --> 00:30:46,580
I think so.

521
00:30:48,410 --> 00:30:49,410
How about...

522
00:30:49,850 --> 00:30:52,520
you try talking it out with him once more?

523
00:30:54,790 --> 00:30:56,380
Okay, Yu-sensei.

524
00:30:57,300 --> 00:30:57,850
Let's go.

525
00:30:59,180 --> 00:31:00,190
Let's give it one more strike.

526
00:31:01,420 --> 00:31:02,410
I'm already exhausted.

527
00:31:02,820 --> 00:31:03,910
Strike the punching bag, not me.

528
00:31:03,940 --> 00:31:04,600
Okay.

529
00:31:04,650 --> 00:31:05,650
It's on you this time, okay?

530
00:31:05,750 --> 00:31:06,280
Let's go.

531
00:31:20,220 --> 00:31:20,980
Guys,

532
00:31:21,560 --> 00:31:22,910
do you think It's impossible
to pry open my mouth?

533
00:31:22,940 --> 00:31:24,720
- No, you're just foul-mouthed.
- No, you're just foul-mouthed.

534
00:31:26,040 --> 00:31:27,110
Whoa...

535
00:31:28,030 --> 00:31:29,030
In unison, too.

536
00:31:31,840 --> 00:31:32,420
So,

537
00:31:32,930 --> 00:31:34,510
what makes you think it's impossible?

538
00:31:36,360 --> 00:31:37,180
I don't know.

539
00:31:37,580 --> 00:31:38,580
Maybe because a friend told me.

540
00:31:40,470 --> 00:31:41,290
Well,

541
00:31:42,660 --> 00:31:43,980
what did you really want to say?

542
00:31:46,150 --> 00:31:46,970
Well...

543
00:31:48,090 --> 00:31:48,920
"Sorry", I guess.

544
00:31:50,300 --> 00:31:50,810
What?

545
00:31:52,180 --> 00:31:53,630
You can say that, after all.

546
00:31:57,290 --> 00:31:58,000
Yeah,

547
00:31:59,510 --> 00:32:00,170
you're right.

548
00:32:01,010 --> 00:32:01,630
What?

549
00:32:02,490 --> 00:32:04,770
Are you in love?

550
00:32:04,820 --> 00:32:06,750
Aha!!

551
00:32:06,910 --> 00:32:07,910
In love?

552
00:32:08,250 --> 00:32:09,030
That's nonsense.

553
00:32:09,720 --> 00:32:11,900
Oh, look at him. "That's nonsense."

554
00:32:13,660 --> 00:32:14,700
Hey, Tai.

555
00:32:15,210 --> 00:32:16,120
My turn now.

556
00:32:17,300 --> 00:32:17,770
Go on.

557
00:32:18,590 --> 00:32:20,480
Moo seems very worried
about his older sister.

558
00:32:20,970 --> 00:32:21,920
That Lhee girl,

559
00:32:22,290 --> 00:32:23,530
is she really that terrifying?

560
00:32:26,260 --> 00:32:28,020
Terrifying doesn't begin to cover it.

561
00:32:28,820 --> 00:32:30,000
Moo's sister

562
00:32:30,710 --> 00:32:31,890
is so damn brutal!

563
00:32:34,960 --> 00:32:36,460
- Whoa, snacks.
- Yeah, take it all.

564
00:32:36,500 --> 00:32:37,970
They're my favorite.
How did you know that?

565
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:39,150
- Moo-Moo,
- Thank you so much.

